(thirdQuint)Trastuzumab in Treating Women With Metastatic Breast Cancer.

 OBJECTIVES: Primary - To evaluate the predictive value of genetic factors on the toxicity and efficacy of a trastuzumab-based therapy in women with metastatic breast cancer.

 Secondary - To analyze tumor factors potentially related to the efficacy of trastuzumab (i.

e.

, expression of proteins involved in cell proliferation and survival).

 OUTLINE: This is a multicenter study.

 Patients receive standard treatment with trastuzumab.

 Blood is collected periodically for pharmacogenetic analysis.

